## Request Lifecycle

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant C as Client
    participant COR as CorrelationId
    participant RL as RateLimit
    participant AUD as Audit
    participant LOG as Logging
    participant R as Router
    participant DI as Dishka
    participant S as ItemService
    participant UoW as UnitOfWork
    participant REPO as ItemRepo
    participant DB as Database

    C->>COR: HTTP Request
    COR->>COR: Extract or generate X-Request-ID
    COR->>RL: Forward request
    RL->>RL: Check token bucket
    RL->>AUD: Forward or reject 429
    AUD->>LOG: Forward request
    LOG->>LOG: Start timer
    LOG->>R: Forward request

    R->>DI: Resolve dependencies
    DI->>DI: Authenticate via Keycloak or Dev
    DI->>DI: Create tenant-scoped AuthUnitOfWork
    DI->>S: Inject ItemService with UoW

    S->>UoW: Enter async context
    UoW->>UoW: Open session
    UoW->>REPO: Get ItemRepository
    REPO->>DB: Execute tenant-scoped SQL
    DB-->>REPO: Result rows
    REPO-->>S: Pydantic domain models
    S->>UoW: Exit context - auto commit

    S-->>R: Response DTO
    R-->>LOG: HTTP Response
    LOG->>LOG: Log method, path, status, duration
    LOG-->>AUD: Forward response
    AUD->>AUD: Log audit record
    AUD-->>COR: Forward response
    COR->>COR: Set X-Request-ID header
    COR-->>C: HTTP Response
```

