Set `ENV` to control which YAML overlay is loaded:

```bash
ENV=development    # config/default.yaml + config/development.yaml
ENV=production     # config/default.yaml + config/production.yaml
ENV=testing        # config/default.yaml + config/testing.yaml
```

### Environment Variable Overrides

All config fields can be overridden via env vars with `APP__` prefix and `__` nesting:

```bash
APP__DB__URL=postgresql+asyncpg://user:pass@host/db
APP__DB__POOL_SIZE=20
APP__SECURITY__AUTH__ENABLED=true
APP__SERVER__PORT=8080
```

### Key Configuration Sections

| Section | Fields | Purpose |
|---------|--------|---------|
| `app` | title, version, description, contact | FastAPI metadata |
| `server` | host, port, cors, workers, log_level | Uvicorn settings |
| `db` | url, pool_size, max_overflow, pool_timeout, echo, ssl_mode | SQLAlchemy engine |
| `security` | secret_key, auth (server_url, realm, client_id, enabled) | JWT + Keycloak |
| `discovery` | enabled, app_name, service_url, instance_* | Eureka registration |
| `logging` | version, formatters, handlers, loggers, root | Python dictConfig |
| `audit` | enabled, excluded_paths, excluded_methods | Audit middleware |

### Development Mode

When `security.auth.enabled=false`, the `DevAuthProvider` is used:
- No Keycloak instance required
- All requests auto-authenticate as a default dev user
- OAuth2 bearer token header is optional

## Testing

### Strategy

| Layer | Approach | Database | Auth |
|-------|----------|----------|------|
| **Unit** | Mock UoW + repositories | None | None |
| **Integration** | Real FastAPI + DI | In-memory SQLite | FakeUser injected |

### Running Tests

```bash
# All tests
uv run pytest -v

# Unit tests only
uv run pytest tests/unit/ -v

# Integration tests only
uv run pytest tests/integration/ -v

# With coverage
uv run pytest --cov=src --cov-report=html
```

### Test Fixtures

**Unit** (`tests/unit/conftest.py`):
- `fake_user` — `FakeUser(id, customer_id, email, roles)`
- `fake_account` — `Account` with known UUIDs
- `async_uow_mock` — `AsyncMock` supporting `async with`

**Integration** (`tests/integration/conftest.py`):
- `async_engine` — `sqlite+aiosqlite:///:memory:` with auto `create_all`
- `session_factory` — test `async_sessionmaker`
- `test_app` — FastAPI app with overridden Dishka container
- `client` — `httpx.AsyncClient` pointing at the test app

